# piml: Physics-Informed Machine Learning #


*piml* is an open-source package designed to easily integrate physical models with machine learning. This project is being developed at Xin Research Group, and is released under the GNU General Public License.  *piml* allows for the physical representation of active sites, enabling the user to specify or create feature and machine learning methods.

This project lives at:
https://github.com/hlxin/piml

Documentation lives at:
https://github.com/hlxin/piml/docs

Users' mailing list lives at:
??
(Subscribe page:)
??

If you would like to compile a local version of the documentation, see the README file in the docs directory.


